      • lookupAnnotatedElements

        protected abstract java.util.Map<E,​java.util.List<A>> lookupAnnotatedElements​(java.lang.Object controller)
        Overriding methods need to return a map, where the key is the annotated element (e.g. field, method) and the value is a list of (potentially repeatable) annotations. In case the annotation is not repeatable, than e list with size 1 is returned, containing the single annotation.
        Parameters:
        controller - the controller instance to extend
        Returns:
        the map of annotated elements and their corresponding annotations (potentially repeatable)

      • extend

        protected abstract void extend​(java.lang.Object controller,
                               E annotatedElement,
                               A annotation)
        The actual extension logic is implemented in this method, which receives the controller instance, as well as the annotated element and one annotation.
        Parameters:
        controller - the controller instance
        annotatedElement - the annotated element (e.g. field or method)
        annotation - the annotation applied to the annotated element

        protected ControlWrapper createControlWrapper​(java.lang.String controlId,
                                              View view)
        Creates a ControlWrapper for a control identified by controlId. The control with the given ID is supposed to by inside the given view.
        Parameters:
